video.title: Nailed It!
video.synopsis: Home bakers with a terrible track record take a crack at re-creating edible masterpieces for a $10,000 prize. It's part reality contest, part hot mess.

episodes.synopsis: A funny, furry pet theme finds the cooks concocting giant exotic-animal cookies, then re-creating Nicole’s adorable dog, Clyde, in cake form.
episodes.title: Im-Paw-sible Cakes

episodes.synopsis: The bakers make candy apple aliens and a sculpted Loch Ness monster cake based on mysterious creatures from outer space... and the freshwater depths.
episodes.title: Paranormal Pastries

episodes.synopsis: Treats inspired by "Mr. Chocolate" Jacques Torres include lollipop portraits and a cake spiced with cocoa and cayenne. Mais oui laugh? But of course!
episodes.title: C’est Jacques!

episodes.synopsis: From cupcakes celebrating famous Black women to a towering Tuskegee Airmen cake, this episode honoring Black history aims high — and achieves hilarity.
episodes.title: History in the Baking

episodes.synopsis: Terrible bakers take on a trio of festive holiday-hat mini cakes before tackling a pop-up Groundhog Day cake that's full of surprises.
episodes.title: There's a Party in My Mouth!

episodes.synopsis: A gardening theme gives life to doughy gnomes atop miniature pies and a healthy-ish veggie-patch cake packed with carrots and zucchini.
episodes.title: Everyone Romaine Calm

episodes.synopsis: Stacked Greek god statue cupcakes and snake-headed Medusa makeover cakes take Herculean effort and skill — and these awkward results are epic.
episodes.title: An Ungodly Mess

episodes.synopsis: It's a Ferris wheel of fails as the teams make treats with a state-fair theme — from caramel corn knockdown-doll clowns to roller-coaster cakes.
episodes.title: The Burbank State Fair

episodes.synopsis: Baking duos go off the deep end with desserts inspired by the wonders of the ocean, including marine animal mini cakes and enormous edible octopuses.
episodes.title: We're Gonna Need a Bigger Cake

episodes.synopsis: Putting their own spin on travel, the bakers make terrible spiced-doughnut tourists and deflated hot-air balloon cakes. It's destination disaster.
episodes.title: Travel Dos and Donuts

episodes.synopsis: Candy-jeweled brooch cookies? Inviting cookie-jar cakes? These sugary sweets are just like the ones Grandma used to make — if Grandma couldn't bake.
episodes.title: I've Failed and I Can't Get Up!

episodes.synopsis: From splashy cereal-bowl cakes to towering hamburgers with fries, these attempts at hyperrealistic treats are so bad, you won't believe your eyes.
episodes.title: Can't Believe It's Cake!

episodes.synopsis: Two bookish treats inspired by literature set the bakers up for epic fails: Shakespearean stained-glass window cookies and a pop-up "Moby Dick" cake.
episodes.title: Let’s Get Lit

episodes.synopsis: Edible ice cream boom boxes made with liquid nitrogen and a fresh and fly fondant-covered cake? Oh, snap — that sounds like a '90s challenge.
episodes.title: The One with the '90s Theme

episodes.synopsis: Terror awaits the contestants as they take on two technically demanding desserts: chocolate eggs and a layered sphinx cake, both full of surprises.
episodes.title: Indiana Fails and the Temple of Slop

episodes.synopsis: The bakers go for the gold — and miss masterfully — with sports-medal cookies and an elaborate swim cake that's topped with a waffle cone torch.
episodes.title: Chariots of Failure

episodes.synopsis: Jam-filled animal pastries and a coffeecake shaped like a sloth push the contestants out of their comfort zones — and the results are wild.
episodes.title: Jungle Bungle

episodes.synopsis: A Western-themed round inspires deep-fried cowboy-duck doughnuts, a root beer-infused rodeo cake ... and really bad flavors.
episodes.title: Howdy, Failure!

episodes.synopsis: From self-frosting bubbling beakers to record-breaking rockets, these science-inspired sweets ask the impossible — and invite kids into the kitchen.
episodes.title: The Big Bake Theory

episodes.synopsis: The bakers commit to re-creating wedding day desserts, including wedding band mini-cakes and a Vegas-themed masterpiece with moving parts.
episodes.title: I Do … Hope I Don’t Fail

episodes.synopsis: The bakers summon their not-so-super powers to make Marvel-themed cupcakes with detailed cookie toppers and a daunting "Black Panther" cake.
episodes.title: The Marvel Episode!

episodes.synopsis: What's scarier than a cook who can't read a recipe? A trio of creepy-crawly bug cookies and a terrifying clown cake that tastes like cotton candy.
episodes.title: Cake-O-Phobia

episodes.synopsis: The amateur bakers attempt to imitate the masters with gingerbread self-portraits and a sculpted cake replica of Michelangelo's David.
episodes.title: Masterpiece or Disasterpiece?

episodes.synopsis: The contestants turn back time -- and mangle time management -- with inside-out Neanderthal cupcakes and a tropical-flavored T. rex cake.
episodes.title: Prehistoric Bakes

episodes.synopsis: The pressure's on to make perfectly puffed éclairs and a layered bust of Napoleon Bonaparte for not one but two esteemed French chefs.
episodes.title: Oui Can't Bake!

episodes.synopsis: Two high-fashion challenges put the bakers' hopeless skills to the test: fondant-covered doll cakes and an edible headdress heaped with fruit.
episodes.title: Ready to Wear, Ready to Eat

episodes.synopsis: The contestants raise the bar with two half-baked "high society" challenges: late-night munchie-inspired pancakes and a gravity-defying tea cake.
episodes.title: High Society

episodes.synopsis: It's "happily ever after" or bust when the bakers try to make fairy tale cupcake pops, then stack cakes in the form of a majestic unicorn.
episodes.title: Fictitious and Delicious

episodes.synopsis: The cooks divide and conquer to fill sections of a savory snack stadium before building a cake that looks like a barbecue grill.
episodes.title: Tailgate, Failgate

episodes.synopsis: 'Tis the season to be scary when the bakers try their hands at holiday cookies before constructing an elaborate gingerbread house.
episodes.title: Holi-daze

episodes.synopsis: The contestants face their fears (with very sharp knives) when they carve an animal out of a watermelon and bend cake into the shape of a snake.
episodes.title: Zoo You Bake?

episodes.synopsis: Space-themed challenges throw the hapless bakers for a loop when they're asked to make cosmic cupcakes and a supersized solar system cake.
episodes.title: Out of This World

episodes.synopsis: Five fabulous "Nailed It!" fans visit the test kitchen for a challenge so extra, we had to make it a bonus episode.
episodes.title: Bonus: 3, 2, 1...Ya Not Done!

episodes.synopsis: Under the watchful eyes of an iconic cake designer, contestants decorate complicated cake pops and a bespectacled, three-tiered wedding cake.
episodes.title: First Date to Life Mate

episodes.synopsis: The bakers do their best to make jelly-filled doughnuts fit for a pirate before tackling an edible tower with a princess on top.
episodes.title: Fantasyland

episodes.synopsis: Two daunting desserts -- a chocolate-filled "hot tub" and an open-mouthed shark cake -- have the hapless home cooks struggling to stay afloat.
episodes.title: Head Under Water

episodes.synopsis: Contestants loosen up a food scientist with a cupcake-cocktail pairing before serving him questionable slices of a bubbling volcano cake.
episodes.title: Weird Science

episodes.synopsis: A YouTube star known for her fondant work watches the bakers try to copy two of her most popular Japanese-themed cakes.
episodes.title: Big in Japan

episodes.synopsis: Dogged contestants are seeing double when they're asked to paint their portraits on a cookie before building an edible bust of Donald Trump.
episodes.title: In Your Face!
